sentence: Yet the events — which present a clear danger to communities across the U.S., risking the further spread of a virus — have been promoted extensively by Fox News.

sentence: “LIBERATE MINNESOTA!”

sentence: The origin of the word “dixie” being used to describe the southern states is unknown, but some believe it could have been after Jeremiah Dixon, one of the men who established the Mason-Dixon Line, or after “dix” which was the name of a Louisiana $10 bill before the Civil War.
